JWT Structure

A JWT consists of three parts separated by dots (.).

Header.Payload.Signature

Example:

eyJhbGciOiJIUzI1NiJ9.

eyJzdWIiOiJyYWh1bEBnbWFpbC5jb20ifQ.

abcxyz123signature

1. Header

Contains information about the token.

Example:

{

"alg": "HS256",

"typ": "JWT"

}

· alg → Algorithm used

· typ → Token type

2. Payload

Contains the user information (claims).

Example:

{

"username": "rahul@gmail.com",

"role": "USER"

}

The payload is the data that the backend stores inside the token.

Note: Do not store passwords or sensitive information in the payload because anyone can decode it.

3. Signature

The signature is created using:

· Header

· Payload

· Secret Key

It ensures that the token has not been modified.

