Generate Token

String token = jwtUtil.generateToken("rahul@gmail.com");

This method creates a JWT token for the given user after a successful login.

Extract Username

String username = jwtUtil.extractUsername(token);

This method reads the username stored inside the token.

Validate Token

boolean valid = jwtUtil.validateToken(token);

This method checks:

· Whether the token is valid.

· Whether the token has expired.

· Whether the signature is correct.

If all checks pass, it returns true; otherwise, it returns false.

Common JWT Classes in Spring Boot

JwtService

Contains the business logic for generating and validating JWT tokens.

JwtUtil

A helper (utility) class that provides methods to create, read, and validate JWT tokens.

JwtTokenProvider

Responsible for generating JWT tokens and extracting user information. In many projects, it performs a similar role to JwtUtil.
